Physical science reference sheet.

Force, mass, and motion. Velocity equals displacement over time. Parenthesis, vee equals D over tea, close parenthesis. Acceleration equals final velocity minus initial velocity, over time. Parenthesis, A. equals vee sub eff minus vee sub eye, over tea, close parenthesis. Weight equals mass times acceleration of gravity. Parenthesis, W equals M gee, close parenthesis. Force equals mass times acceleration. Parenthesis, eff equals em A, close parenthesis. Work equals force times distance. Parenthesis, W equals F dee, close parenthesis. Mechanical advantage equals effort distance over resistance distance, equals resistance force over effort force. Parenthesis, em A equals D sub E over D sub are, equals F sub are over F sub ee, close parenthesis.

Chemical reactions and properties of matter. Density equals mass over volume. Parenthesis, dee equals M over vee, close parenthesis. Volume of a rectangular solid equals length times width times height. Parenthesis, V equals L W H, close parenthesis. Heat lost or gained equals mass times specific heat capacity times change in temperature. Parenthesis, Q equals MC delta tea, close parenthesis.
Waves, electricity, and magnetism. Voltage equals current times resistance. Parenthesis, V equals I are, close parenthesis.

Constants and relationships. Kelvin equals degrees celsius plus two hundred seventy three. Parenthesis, K equals degrees see plus two hundred seventy three. Newton. One N equals one K G times M over S squared. Acceleration due to gravity, G is approximately equal to 10 and M over S squared. Joule. One J equals one N time M.
